metadata.name: home before dusk
metadata.description:
as a kid, I'd spend my summer days in tall grass up to my knees, roaming the familiar backwoods behind my home. "home before dusk" is an ode to itchy legs, hazy evenings, cicada sounds, and the familiar phrase from a mother.
